COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | ARRONDISSEMENT N°7 DE BOBO-DIOULASSO | BANA VILLAGE
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Four homes separated by at least 100 m are randomly selected in the village. In each selected home, two peoples sit down, one indoor or outside the house with his lower leg exposed and collects all the mosquitoes that come for a blood meal using a mosquito aspirator. Each mosquito after collection is placed in hemolyze tube plugged with a piece of cotton. The hemolyze tube is then placed in a bag containing information about the time interval of collection, the ID of the collection point. Early in the morning all the bag are sent to the field laboratory for mosquito identification and preservation.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Knocked out in the freezer at - 20 °C for 15 minutes. Preservation1: Grouped in a pool of at most 10 in a 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 4 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.
COLLECTOR_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
IDENTIFIER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
PRESERVER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE

PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Knocked out in the freezer at - 20 °C for 15 minutes. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.

PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Knocked out in the freezer at - 20 °C for 15 minutes. Preservation1: Grouped in a pool of at most 10 in a 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 3 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | ARRONDISSEMENT N°7 DE BOBO-DIOULASSO | BANA VILLAGE
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.
COLLECTOR_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
IDENTIFIER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
PRESERVER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE

Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | ARRONDISSEMENT N°7 DE BOBO-DIOULASSO | BANA VILLAGE
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | ARRONDISSEMENT N°7 DE BOBO-DIOULASSO | BANA VILLAGE
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 4 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | DEPARTEMENT DE KARANGASSO-SAMBLA | SOUROUKOUDINGAN
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: A person sits indoor or outdoor the house with his lower leg exposed and collects all the mosquitoes that come for a blood meal using a mosquito aspirator
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Knocked out in the freezer at - 20 °C for 15 minutes. Preservation1: Grouped in a pool of at most 10 in a 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 3 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.

Preservation1: Grouped in a pool of at most 10 in a 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 3 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | DEPARTEMENT DE KARANGASSO-SAMBLA | SOUROUKOUDINGAN
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.
COLLECTOR_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
IDENTIFIER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
PRESERVER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE

Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | DEPARTEMENT DE KARANGASSO-SAMBLA | SOUROUKOUDINGAN
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | DEPARTEMENT DE KARANGASSO-SAMBLA | SOUROUKOUDINGAN
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: Pyrethroid based-aerosol (Kaltox: an aerosol manufactured by SAPHYTO® and made of 0.20% Tetramethrin, 0.17% Permethrin, 0.75% Chlorpyrifos-ethyl, solvent, propulsor and 98,61% perfume) is sprayed inside the houses early in the morning (mainly at 6:00) after a white sheet is laid to cover the surface of the ground of the houses to collect dead or stunned mosquitoes due to the insecticide's effect. Fifteen minutes after the spraying, the white sheet is brought out from the house and the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected using forceps, placed in petri dishes and send to the field laboratory for morphological identification.
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Kill or knocked out with a pyrethroid based-aerosol (Spraying time: 30 seconds, time elapsed from spraying to collection: 15 minutes). Collection method: All the dead and knocked-down mosquitoes are collected, kept in petri dishes and send to the field lab for morphological identification. Preservation1: Grouped in pool of at most 10 in 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 100% ethanol and stored at room temperature before the shipping.
COLLECTOR_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE
IDENTIFIER_AFFILIATION: INSTITUT DE RECHERCHE EN SCIENCES DE LA SANTE

COLLECTION_LOCATION: BURKINA FASO | HAUTS-BASSINS | HOEUT | ARRONDISSEMENT N°5 DE BOBO-DIOULASSO | PALA
DESCRIPTION_OF_COLLECTION_METHOD: A person sits indoor or outdoor the house with his lower leg exposed and collects all the mosquitoes that come for a blood meal using a mosquito aspirator
PRESERVATION_APPROACH: Kill method: Knocked out in the freezer at - 20 °C for 15 minutes. Preservation1: Grouped in a pool of at most 10 in a 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 4 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.

Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.

Preservation1: Grouped in a pool of at most 10 in a 2 ml eppendorf tube with 80% ethanol (~ 1.6ml) and stored at room temperature for 2 years. Preservation2: moved individually to PCR plate well with 200µl of 80% ethanol and stored at room temperature before shipping.
